title: RealtimeBondage--Double Blind Study Elise Graves Dixon Mason MP4
description:
Double Blind Study | Elise Graves | Dixon Mason

August 24, 2013 


MP4 only. 


Today we have two subjects for our very special study. This study is of endurance. How long can a person be deprived of comfort before they crack? How long can someone be frustrated sexually, emotionally, and physically before they can't take anymore. This "double blind study" will explore these themes. In fact, the subjects of this study are so interested in finding out the answers to these questions that they themselves have volunteered and come up with many of the ideas for their own torture.

The study starts outside. First we must wash our subjects. We would not want a tainted result. Once they are sufficiently clean and shivering we subject them to the first test. Fear. Can they bear the fear of being in an enclosed tub as it slowly fills with water? The result is quite fascinating.

Now that we know the answer to that hypothesis, we turn from water to fire. Can they bear the heat of a crackling fire? Can they bear the heat of fiery capsaicin on their most delicate female bits?

Lastly, sexual service. Now that they have been broken down by cold water and hot fire, how do they fare at pleasing others?

The purely educational answers to these scientific queries and more can be found in this video archive of the beginning of a 26 hour test of mental and physical endurance.
